Interface SocksMethodRequestor

    public interface SocksMethodRequestor
    The interface SocksMethodRequestor is a tool that can send request message from SOCKS server and get a method that server accepted.

    • Method Detail

      • doRequest

        SocksMethod doRequest(List<SocksMethod> acceptableMethods,
                    Socket socket,
                    int socksVersion)
                      throws SocksException,
                             IOException
        Send request message to server.

        This method will send list of methods to SOCKS server and receive the method that SOCKS server selected.

        Parameters:
        acceptableMethods - Methods that client can handle.
        socket - The socket instance that has connected SOCKS server.
        socksVersion - SOCKS protocol version
        Returns:
        Method that server accepted.
        Throws:
        SocksException - If any errors about SOCKS protocol occurred.
        IOException - if any IO errors occurred.
